
Privara Enterprise HIDS operates under GDPR Article 5 principles:

1. **Lawfulness, Fairness, and Transparency**
   - Clear Privacy Policy presented on first launch
   - Explicit consent required for monitoring activation
   - Users can review what data is being collected in real-time

2. **Purpose Limitation**
   - Data collected only for security monitoring purposes
   - No secondary use of personal data
   - No data sharing with third parties
   - All processing stays local on user's machine

3. **Data Minimization**
   - Collect only necessary process and network metadata
   - File content not examined (only file metadata and hashes)
   - No keyboard logging or screen recording
   - Minimal registry monitoring (only security-relevant keys)

4. **Accuracy and Integrity**
   - Regular data validation checks
   - Automatic correction of outdated threat information
   - Version control for configuration files

5. **Storage Limitation**
   - Threat logs: 90 days retention
   - Process history: 30 days retention
   - Configuration: Until user deletion
   - Automatic purging after retention periods
   - Manual override available via "Right to be Forgotten"

6. **Integrity and Confidentiality**
   - AES-256 encryption for sensitive configuration
   - Local storage only (no cloud sync)
   - No external API calls or telemetry
   - Hash verification for critical files

### User Rights Implementation

**Article 15 - Right of Access**
- Menu option: "Export All My Data"
- Generates JSON file with all user-created data within 30 days
- Includes: Configuration, whitelist/blacklist, alerts, scan history

**Article 16 - Right to Rectification**
- Settings allow direct modification of monitored rules
- Users can correct process classifications
- Manual override system for detected threats

**Article 17 - Right to Erasure (Right to be Forgotten)**
- One-click "Delete All Personal Data" button
- 24-hour reversal window (data stored in recovery partition)
- Automatic purge after 24 hours
- Legally required security logs preserved
- Confirmation email-style notification with reversal PIN

**Article 20 - Right to Data Portability**
- "Export Configuration" feature exports all settings as portable JSON
- Import to other Privara installations
- No proprietary file formats

**Article 21 - Right to Object**
- Per-component monitoring disable options
- Users can disable specific HIDS modules
- Save configuration as profile for later reactivation

### Compliance Certifications

**GDPR Compliance Checklist**
- ☑ Privacy Policy: Embedded in application, no external links
- ☑ Data Protection Impact Assessment (DPIA): Reference documentation included
- ☑ Data Processing Agreement template available
- ☑ Legitimate Interest Assessment available
- ☑ Data breach notification: Provided if vulnerabilities detected
- ☑ Privacy by Design: No telemetry, local processing only
- ☑ Data retention schedules: Clear time limits for all data types
- ☑ Consent mechanism: Explicit opt-in for monitoring modules
- ☑ User rights implementation: All Articles 15-22 supported

**Other Compliance Standards**
- CCPA (California Consumer Privacy Act): Supported
- LGPD (Brazilian Data Protection Law): Supported
- HIPAA-compatible (secure local processing)
- ISO 27001-aligned security practices

---

## PACKAGING AS .EXE WITH INSTALLATION WIZARD

### Prerequisites for .exe Creation
The following tools and frameworks are recommended:

1. **Electron Packaging** (NOT RECOMMENDED for security app)
   - Too heavyweight for system utility
   - Large download size (150-300MB)
   - High memory footprint

2. **NW.js** (Better alternative)
   - Smaller footprint than Electron (80-150MB)
   - Better performance for system monitoring
   - Security features: Content Security Policy, Sandboxing

3. **NSIS (Nullsoft Scriptable Install System)** (RECOMMENDED)
   - Creates professional .exe installer
   - Small download (50-100MB for bundled app)
   - Support for .NET runtime integration
   - Custom license page with GDPR terms
   - Multi-language installer support
   - Post-installation tasks (service setup, firewall rules)

4. **Advanced Installer** (ENTERPRISE OPTION)
   - Full GDPR compliance wizard
   - Digital signing
   - Automatic updates
   - System restore point creation

### Installation Wizard Flow (NSIS/Advanced Installer)

```
Step 1: Welcome Screen
├─ Show Privara logo with techno-punk aesthetic
├─ Highlight key features
└─ "Next" to continue

Step 2: License & GDPR Agreement
├─ GDPR Compliance Notice (required read)
├─ Terms of Service (required acceptance)
├─ Privacy Policy (collapsible)
├─ Checkbox: "I agree to GDPR Data Processing Terms"
└─ Cannot proceed without acceptance

Step 3: Data Processing Consent
├─ Explain what data will be collected
├─ List retention periods
├─ Allow opt-in/opt-out for telemetry
├─ Explain anonymization features
└─ Show data deletion options

Step 4: Installation Options
├─ Installation path selection
├─ Start menu shortcuts
├─ Desktop shortcut (optional)
├─ Auto-start with Windows (opt-in)
├─ System Service installation (checkbox)
└─ Windows Firewall configuration (automatic)

Step 5: Performance Profile Selection
├─ "Balanced" (default) - Chandrahas profile
├─ "Aggressive" - Maximum monitoring
├─ "Conservative" - Minimal overhead
└─ "Custom" - Manual configuration

Step 6: Theme Selection
├─ Midnight (default)
├─ Luminescence
├─ AMOLED Black
├─ Twilight
├─ Neon Retro
└─ Custom Theme Builder (preview included)

Step 7: Timezone & Locale
├─ Timezone selection dropdown
├─ Language selection (English, French options)
├─ 12/24 hour format selector
└─ Number format preference

Step 8: User Profile Setup
├─ Create initial user profile
├─ Enter profile name (default: "Chandrahas")
├─ Set admin password (required)
├─ Enable/disable specific monitoring modules
└─ Save profile for import on other machines

Step 9: System Requirements Check
├─ Verify Windows 10/11
├─ Check administrator rights
├─ Verify free disk space (minimum 500MB)
├─ Confirm .NET Framework / Windows Runtime availability
└─ Alert if antivirus conflicts detected

Step 10: Pre-Installation Summary
├─ Review all selections
├─ Final GDPR confirmation
├─ Option to create restore point
├─ "Install" button

Step 11: Installation Progress
├─ Progress bar with file counts
├─ Sub-tasks: Registry entries, Service setup, Firewall rules
├─ Real-time log of installation steps
└─ Show option to "View Detailed Log"

Step 12: Post-Installation
├─ Success notification
├─ Launch application checkbox
├─ "Create Desktop Shortcut" option
├─ "View Release Notes" link
├─ Finish button
```

### NSIS Script Template

```nsis
; Privara Enterprise HIDS Installer
; NSIS 3.x

!include "MUI2.nsh"
!include "Sections.nsh"
!include "x64.nsh"

; Define constants
!define PRODUCT_NAME "Privara Enterprise HIDS"
!define PRODUCT_VERSION "1.0.0"
!define PRODUCT_PUBLISHER "Privara Security"
!define PRODUCT_UNINST_KEY "Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Uninstall\${PRODUCT_NAME}"

; Basic settings
SetCompressor lzma
ShowInstDetails show
ShowUninstDetails show

; Default installation folder
InstallDir "$PROGRAMFILES\Privara"

; Get installation folder from registry if available
InstallDirRegKey HKCU "Software\Privara" "InstallDir"

; MUI Settings
!insertmacro MUI_PAGE_WELCOME
!insertmacro MUI_PAGE_LICENSE "LICENSE.txt"
Page custom GDPRPage
Page custom DataConsentPage
!insertmacro MUI_PAGE_DIRECTORY
Page custom PerformanceProfilePage
Page custom ThemeSelectionPage
Page custom TimezoneLocatePage
Page custom UserProfilePage
!insertmacro MUI_PAGE_INSTFILES
!insertmacro MUI_PAGE_FINISH

!insertmacro MUI_LANGUAGE "English"
!insertmacro MUI_LANGUAGE "French"

; Installer sections
Section "Privara HIDS Core" SEC_CORE
  SetOutPath "$INSTDIR"
  File /r "dist\*.*"
  
  ; Create Start Menu shortcuts
  CreateDirectory "$SMPROGRAMS\Privara"
  CreateShortCut "$SMPROGRAMS\Privara\Privara.lnk" "$INSTDIR\Privara.exe"
  CreateShortCut "$SMPROGRAMS\Privara\Uninstall.lnk" "$INSTDIR\uninstall.exe"
  
  ; Write registry keys
  WriteRegStr HKCU "Software\Privara" "InstallDir" "$INSTDIR"
  WriteRegStr HKCU "Software\Privara" "Version" "${PRODUCT_VERSION}"
  WriteRegStr HKCU "Software\Privara" "InstallDate" "$%DATE%"
  
  ; Create uninstaller
  WriteUninstaller "$INSTDIR\uninstall.exe"
SectionEnd

Section "Windows Service" SEC_SERVICE
  ${If} ${RunningX64}
    ExecWait '"$INSTDIR\PrivaraService.exe" /install'
  ${EndIf}
SectionEnd

; GDPR custom page
Function GDPRPage
  !insertmacro MUI_HEADER_TEXT "GDPR Compliance" "Review our data processing practices"
  
  GetDlgItem $0 $HWNDPARENT 1 ; Get Next button
  EnableWindow $0 0 ; Disable until accepted
  
  ; Show GDPR disclaimer and terms
  ; User must check acceptance checkbox to proceed
FunctionEnd

; Data Consent page
Function DataConsentPage
  !insertmacro MUI_HEADER_TEXT "Data Processing Consent" "What data will we collect?"
  
  ; Display retention periods
  ; Display what data is collected
  ; Allow opt-in/opt-out for specific modules
FunctionEnd

; Performance Profile page
Function PerformanceProfilePage
  !insertmacro MUI_HEADER_TEXT "Select Performance Profile" "Choose monitoring intensity"
  
  ; Radio buttons for: Balanced, Aggressive, Conservative, Custom
FunctionEnd

; Theme Selection page
Function ThemeSelectionPage
  !insertmacro MUI_HEADER_TEXT "Select Theme" "Choose your preferred aesthetic"
  
  ; Radio buttons for: Midnight, Luminescence, AMOLED Black, Twilight, Neon Retro
FunctionEnd

; Timezone & Locale page
Function TimezoneLocatePage
  !insertmacro MUI_HEADER_TEXT "Timezone & Language" "Configure regional settings"
  
  ; Dropdown for timezone selection
  ; Dropdown for language selection
FunctionEnd

; User Profile page
Function UserProfilePage
  !insertmacro MUI_HEADER_TEXT "Create User Profile" "Set up your security profile"
  
  ; Text field for profile name
  ; Password fields for admin credentials
  ; Checkboxes for module selection
FunctionEnd

; Uninstaller section
Section "Uninstall"
  ; Remove registry keys
  DeleteRegKey HKCU "Software\Privara"
  
  ; Remove files
  RMDir /r "$INSTDIR"
  RMDir /r "$SMPROGRAMS\Privara"
  
  ; Remove desktop shortcut if exists
  Delete "$DESKTOP\Privara.lnk"
  
  ; Stop service if running
  ExecWait '"$INSTDIR\PrivaraService.exe" /uninstall'
SectionEnd
```

### Code Signing for .exe

```batch
; Sign installer with EV certificate (Recommended)
signtool sign /f "certificate.pfx" /p "password" /d "Privara Enterprise HIDS" ^
  /du "https://privara-security.com" /t "http://timestamp.server.com" ^
  Privara-Setup-1.0.0.exe

; Verify signature
signtool verify /v /pa Privara-Setup-1.0.0.exe
```

---

## SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS FOR .EXE

**Minimum Requirements:**
- Windows 10 Build 19041 or Windows 11
- Intel Core i3 / AMD Ryzen 3 (or equivalent)
- 4GB RAM
- 500MB free disk space
- .NET Framework 4.8 or .NET 6.0 Runtime
- Administrator privileges for installation

**Recommended Requirements:**
- Windows 11 Build 22621 or later
- Intel Core i7 / AMD Ryzen 7
- 8GB RAM
- SSD with 1GB free space
- Hyper-V capable processor (for sandboxing features)

---

## DISTRIBUTION & UPDATE STRATEGY

### Primary Distribution
1. GitHub Releases (open-source)
2. Windows Store listing (verified publisher)
3. Company website download (with code signing verification)

### Automatic Updates
- Built-in update checker (runs weekly)
- Prompt user for critical security updates
- Staged rollout: 10% → 50% → 100% of user base
- Rollback mechanism if critical issues detected

### Version Control
- Version format: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`
- Changelog maintained in release notes
- Breaking changes documented clearly
- GDPR impact assessment for each update

---

## SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS FOR DISTRIBUTION

1. **Code Signing**: All .exe files digitally signed with EV certificate
2. **Hash Verification**: SHA-256 hashes provided for all releases
3. **SBOM (Software Bill of Materials)**: Provided with each release for supply chain transparency
4. **Vulnerability Disclosure**: Responsible disclosure policy in place
5. **Security Audit**: Third-party security audit recommended before initial release

